|WKBNAME|000
    remove_shield

|WKBSYNOPSIS|000
    |YK0void|000 |CKBremove_shield|000(|YK0int|000 |GKBiAmount|000)
    |YK0void|000 |CKBremove_shield|000(|YK0int|000 |GKBiAmount|000, |YK0int|000 |GKBiType|000)

|WKBDESCRIPTION|000
    Decrease a living creature/player's shield for damage

    |GKBiAmount|000 is the amount of damage being removed from the shield [Required]
    NOTE: there is no such thing as a negative shield. A shield with
    value less than 0 ceases to function as a shield.

    |GKBiType|000 is an optional parameter (|YK0bitmask|000) specifying the type of
    damage the shield will block/absorb.  If not specified, this shield
    will block all types of damage. May be useful to check <types.h>

    |CKBremove_shield|000() is defined in /secure/living.c

|WKBSEE ALSO|000
    |CKBset_shield|000(L), |CKBquery_shield|000(L), |CKBremove_shield|000(L)


